{
  "text": "NIH 3T3 fibroblasts were incubated with a range of concentrations of SMIFH2 to determine its effects on adherent mammalian cells. Cell viability was assessed after 24 hr. SMIFH2 elicited cytotoxicity with an IC 50 of 28 mM ( Figure 6A ). We also observed dose-dependent growth inhibition of NIH 3T3 fibroblasts within a period of 96 hr ( Figure 6B ). In addition, cells cultured in SMIFH2 with concentrations as low as 2.5 mM were observed to have cytokinesis defects, as measured by the percentage of multinucleated cells. After 4 days, 8.6 \u00b1 2% of cells cultured in 2.5 mM SMIFH2 had multiple nuclei as compared to 1.1 \u00b1 0.7% of cells treated with a DMSO control. This cytokinesis defect is consistent with recent data showing that siRNA depletion of mDia2 in NIH 3T3 fibroblasts increases the percentage of binucleate cells to 35% [CITATION_1] .",
